50enum class ExprPrecedence : int {
51 /*! \brief Identity(e.g., IntImm, Var) and function call(e.g., floordiv, min) */
52 kIdentity = 0,
53 /*!
54 * \brief Multiplication(*), division(/), and remainder(%)
55 * \note floorDiv, floorMod is marked as kIdentity since they are function calls.
56 */
57 kMultiplicationDivision = 1,
58 /*! \brief Addition(+) and subtraction(-) */
59 kAdditionSubtraction = 2,
60 /*! \brief For relational operators < and <= and > and >= respectively */
61 kRelational = 3,
62 /*! \brief For equality operators = and != respectively */
63 kEquality = 4,
64 /*! \brief And(&&) */
65 kAnd = 5,
66 /*! \brief Or(||) */
67 kOr = 6,
68 /*! \brief Unknown precedence */
69 kUnknown = 7,
70};
71
72/*! \brief Utility used for identifying usage of a buffer_var
73 *
74 * \details Find the Buffer object that corresponds to a variable or
75 * allocation, based on the BufferLoad/BufferStore instances that
76 * occur within the allocation's body.
77 */
78class BufferUsageFinder : public StmtExprVisitor {
79 public:
80 static Map<Var, Array<Buffer>> FindUsage(Map<Var, Array<Buffer>> usage, Stmt body) {
81 BufferUsageFinder visitor(std::move(usage));
82 visitor.VisitStmt(body);
83 return std::move(visitor.usage_);
84 }
85
86 void VisitExpr_(const VarNode* op) final {
87 Var var = GetRef<Var>(op);
88 if (!usage_.count(var)) {
89 usage_.Set(var, {});
90 }
91 }
92
93 void VisitExpr_(const BufferLoadNode* op) final {
94 VisitBuffer(op->buffer);
95 StmtExprVisitor::VisitExpr_(op);
96 }
97
98 void VisitStmt_(const BufferStoreNode* op) final {
99 VisitBuffer(op->buffer);
100 StmtExprVisitor::VisitStmt_(op);
101 }
102
103 void VisitStmt_(const DeclBufferNode* op) final {
104 buffers_declared_.insert(op->buffer.get());
105 StmtExprVisitor::VisitStmt_(op);
106 buffers_declared_.erase(op->buffer.get());
107 }
108
109 private:
110 explicit BufferUsageFinder(Map<Var, Array<Buffer>> usage) : usage_(usage) {}
111
112 void VisitBuffer(const Buffer& buffer) {
113 if (buffers_visited_.count(buffer.get())) {
114 return;
115 }
116 if (buffers_declared_.count(buffer.get())) {
117 return;
118 }
119 buffers_visited_.insert(buffer.get());
120
121 Array<Buffer> arr = usage_.Get(buffer->data).value_or({});
122 arr.push_back(buffer);
123 usage_.Set(buffer->data, arr);
124 }
125
126 // The search result.
127 Map<Var, Array<Buffer>> usage_;
128 // The buffers that have been visited so far, to avoid duplicate
129 // entries in the search result.
130 std::unordered_set<const BufferNode*> buffers_visited_;
131 // The buffers declared via `DeclBuffer`. These buffers are excluded from the result because
132 // T.buffer_decl shouldn't be printed for them.
133 std::unordered_set<const BufferNode*> buffers_declared_;
134};

136/*!
137 * \brief The printer for TVMScript
138 * \details The printer obtain the precedence of the top-level operation when printing each
139 * subexpression to decide whether or not parentheses is needed.
140 */
141class TVMScriptPrinter : public StmtFunctor<Doc(const Stmt&)>,
142 public ExprFunctor<Doc(const PrimExpr&, ExprPrecedence*)>,
143 public TypeFunctor<Doc(const Type&)> {
144 public:
145 explicit TVMScriptPrinter(const String& tir_prefix, bool show_meta,
146 runtime::TypedPackedFunc<std::string(Stmt)> annotate = nullptr)
147 : tir_prefix_(tir_prefix),
148 show_meta_(show_meta),
149 annotate_(std::move(annotate)),
150 meta_collector_(&meta_) {}

159
160 protected:

163 /*! \brief whether show meta data */

167 /*! \brief meta data context */

169 /*! \brief meta collector */

173 /*! \brief var collector (var defined by For/Loop/Block) */
174 std::unordered_set<const VarNode*> var_not_in_headers_;

176 * \brief buffer collector
177 * (buffer defined in BufferMap, BufferAllocation and MatchBufferRegion)
178 */

188 /*! \brief name allocation map */

208 *
209 * Used for identifying buffers that should be declared after the
210 * LetStmt or Allocate that generates their data pointer, rather
211 * than in the header.
212 */
213 Map<Var, Array<Buffer>> buffer_var_usage_;
214 /*! \brief Analyzer to simplify some expressions. */
215 arith::Analyzer ana_;

305 * \brief Check if a buffer declaration satisfies:
306 * 1. has only 'shape' and 'dtype' arguments specified,
307 * 2. the shape and strides are not dynamic.

314 /*! Helper functions for loop printing. */
315 /*!
316 * \brief Print a single for loop
317 * \param loop The for loop to be printed
318 */
319 virtual Doc PrintLoop(const For& loop);
320 /*! \brief Print all simple loops in stack into one line using tir_prefix_.grid(). */
321 Doc PrintLoopStack();
322 /*!
323 * \brief Check whether a loop satisfies:
324 * 1. the loop is serial;
325 * 2. the loop has no annotation;
326 * 3. the loop starts from 0;
327 * 4. there is no optional information.
328 * \param for_op the for node to be checked
329 * \return A boolean indicating whether the input loop satisfies the above conditions
330 */
331 bool IsSimpleLoop(const ForNode* for_op) {
332 return for_op->kind == ForKind::kSerial && for_op->annotations.empty() &&
333 is_zero(for_op->min) && !ContainsOptionalInfo(GetRef<Stmt>(for_op));
334 }
335 /*!
336 * \brief Check whether the `min` or `extent` of a loop depends on previous loops
337 * \param for_op The loop to be checked
338 * \return A boolean indicating whether the input loop depends on previous loops
339 */
340 bool DependOnPrevLoops(const ForNode* for_op) {
341 auto f_check = [&var_map = this->loop_var_map_](const VarNode* v) { return var_map.count(v); };
342 return UsesVar(for_op->min, f_check) || UsesVar(for_op->extent, f_check);
343 }
344
345 /*!
346 * \brief Print additional info about expr in comment.
347 * \param expr The expression.
348 */
349 Doc PrintOptionalInfo(const Stmt& stmt) {
350 Doc doc;
351 // default annotations
352 if (ContainsOptionalInfo(stmt)) {
353 std::string annotated_stmt = annotate_(stmt);
354 doc << "# " << annotated_stmt << Doc::NewLine();
355 }
356 return doc;
357 }
358
359 /*!
360 * \brief special method to render vectors of docs with a separator
361 * \param vec vector of docs
362 * \param sep separator
363 */
364 static Doc PrintSep(const std::vector<Doc>& vec, const Doc& sep) {
365 Doc seq;
366 if (vec.size() != 0) {
367 seq = vec[0];
368 for (size_t i = 1; i < vec.size(); i++) {
369 seq << sep << vec[i];
370 }
371 }
372 return seq;
373 }
374
375 /*!
376 * \brief dump meta info
377 * \return Doc with meta info
378 */
379 Doc DumpMeta() {
380 if (show_meta_) {
381 return Doc::Text("__tvm_meta__ = ")
382 << (meta_.empty() ? Doc::Text("None") : meta_.GetMetaSection());
383 } else {
384 return Doc::Text("");
385 }
386 }
387
388 /*!
389 * \brief special method to print out data type
390 * \param dtype The data type
391 */
392 static Doc PrintDType(DataType dtype) {
393 return Doc::StrLiteral(runtime::DLDataType2String(dtype));
394 }
395
396 /*!
397 * \brief special method to print out const int64_t scalar
398 * \param dtype The data type
399 * \param data The pointer to hold the data.
400 */
401 Doc PrintConstScalar(DataType dtype, const int64_t* data) const {
402 Doc doc;
403 std::ostringstream os;
404
405 os << data[0];
406
407 if (dtype == DataType::Int(32)) {
408 doc << Doc::Text(os.str());
409 } else if (dtype == DataType::Bool()) {
410 doc << Doc::Text(data[0] ? "True" : "False");
411 } else {
412 doc << tir_prefix_ << "." << runtime::DLDataType2String(dtype) << "(" << Doc::Text(os.str())
413 << ")";
414 }
415 return doc;
416 }
417
418 /*!
419 * \brief special method to print out const double scalar
420 * \param dtype The data type
421 * \param data The pointer to hold the data.
422 * \note this overriden function is created as std::isnan of msvc will complain about int64_t
423 */
424 Doc PrintConstScalar(DataType dtype, const double* data) const {
425 Doc doc;
426 std::ostringstream os;
427
428 os.precision(17);
429 if (std::isinf(data[0]) || std::isnan(data[0])) {
430 os << "\"" << data[0] << "\"";
431 } else {
432 os << data[0];
433 }
434
435 doc << tir_prefix_ << "." << runtime::DLDataType2String(dtype) << "(" << Doc::Text(os.str())
436 << ")";
437
438 return doc;
439 }
440
441 public:
442 static Doc PrintHeader(const std::string& tir_prefix) {
443 Doc header;
444 if (tir_prefix != "tir") {
445 header << "# from tvm.script import tir as " << tir_prefix << Doc::NewLine();
446 } else {
447 header << "# from tvm.script import tir" << Doc::NewLine();
448 }
449 return header;
450 }
451};

453/*!
454 * \brief special method to print NDArray in TIR
455 * \param arr the NDArray to be printed
456 * \param os the output stream where the NDArray will be printed to
457 */
458template <typename T>
459void NDArrayToTIR(::tvm::runtime::NDArray arr, std::ostream& os) {
460 int ndim = arr->ndim;
461 int tot_dim = 1;
462 for (int i = 0; i < ndim; i++) {
463 tot_dim *= arr->shape[i];
464 }
465 T* data_ptr = reinterpret_cast<T*>(arr->data);
466 constexpr int NUM_PRINT = 20;
467 os << "[";
468 for (int i = 0; i < tot_dim; i++) {
469 os << (i != 0 ? ", " : "") << data_ptr[i];
470 if (i == NUM_PRINT) {
471 os << "...";
472 break;
473 }
474 }
475 os << "]";
476}
477
478Doc TVMScriptPrinter::GetUniqueName(std::string prefix) {
479 std::replace(prefix.begin(), prefix.end(), '.', '_');
480 std::string unique_prefix = prefix;
481 auto it = name_alloc_map_.find(prefix);
482 if (it != name_alloc_map_.end() && it->second >= 0) {
483 while (name_alloc_map_.count(unique_prefix = prefix + "_" + std::to_string(++it->second)) > 0) {
484 }
485 }
486 name_alloc_map_[unique_prefix] = 0;
487 return Doc::Text(unique_prefix);
488}
489
490Doc TVMScriptPrinter::AllocVar(const Var& var) {
491 const auto& it = memo_var_.find(var);
492 if (it != memo_var_.end()) {
493 return it->second;
494 }
495 std::string name = var->name_hint.operator std::string();
496 if (name.length() == 0 || !std::isalpha(name[0])) {
497 name = "v" + name;
498 }
499 Doc val = GetUniqueName(name);
500 memo_var_[var] = val;
501 return val;
502}
503
504Doc TVMScriptPrinter::AllocBufferDeclaration(const Buffer& buf) {
505 Doc doc = Print(buf->shape);
506 bool print_factor_explicitly = false;
507 doc << ", dtype=" << PrintDType(buf->dtype);
508 if (memo_var_.find(buf->data) != memo_var_.end()) {
509 doc << ", data=" << Print(buf->data);
510 } else {
511 // implicitly define data
512 memo_var_[buf->data] = Doc::Text(memo_buf_[buf].str() + ".data");
513 var_not_in_headers_.insert(buf->data.get());
514 }
515 if (!buf->strides.empty()) {
516 doc << ", strides=" << Print(buf->strides);
517 }
518 if (buf->elem_offset->IsInstance<VarNode>()) {
519 Var elem_offset = Downcast<Var>(buf->elem_offset);
520 if (memo_var_.find(elem_offset) != memo_var_.end()) {
521 doc << ", elem_offset=" << Print(buf->elem_offset);
522 } else {
523 // implicitly define elem_offset
524 memo_var_[elem_offset] = Doc::Text(memo_buf_[buf].str() + ".elem_offset");
525 var_not_in_headers_.insert(elem_offset.get());
526 print_factor_explicitly = true;
527 }
528 } else if (buf->elem_offset->IsInstance<IntImmNode>()) {
529 IntImm elem_offset = Downcast<IntImm>(buf->elem_offset);
530 if (elem_offset->value != 0) {
531 doc << ", elem_offset=" << Print(buf->elem_offset);
532 }
533 }
534 if (buf.scope() != "global") {
535 doc << ", scope=" << Doc::StrLiteral(buf.scope());
536 }
537 if (buf->data_alignment != runtime::kAllocAlignment) {
538 doc << ", align=" << buf->data_alignment;
539 }
540 if (buf->offset_factor != 1 || print_factor_explicitly) {
541 doc << ", offset_factor=" << buf->offset_factor;
542 }
543 if (buf->buffer_type != BufferType::kDefault) {
544 doc << ", type=" << Doc::StrLiteral("auto");
545 }
546 if (buf->axis_separators.size()) {
547 doc << ", axis_separators=" << Print(buf->axis_separators);
548 }
549 return doc;
550}
551
552Doc TVMScriptPrinter::AllocBuf(const Buffer& buffer) {
553 const auto& it = memo_buf_.find(buffer);
554 if (it != memo_buf_.end()) {
555 return it->second;
556 }
557 std::string name = buffer->name;
558 if (name.length() == 0 || !std::isalpha(name[0])) {
559 name = "buf_" + name;
560 }
561 Doc val = GetUniqueName(name);
562 memo_buf_[buffer] = val;
563 memo_buf_decl_[buffer] = AllocBufferDeclaration(buffer);
564 return val;
565}
566
567/*!
568 * \brief Check if any optional information exists in annotate_ for
569 * a given Stmt.
570 * \param stmt The statement.
571 */
572bool TVMScriptPrinter::ContainsOptionalInfo(const Stmt& stmt) {
573 if (annotate_ == nullptr) return false;
574 return !annotate_(stmt).empty();
575}
576
577/*!
578 * \brief Try to dealloc vars out of space and leave the index to coming vars.
579 * \note It is not a necessary step.
580 */
581void TVMScriptPrinter::TryDeallocVar(const Var& var) {
582 auto it = memo_var_.find(var);
583 ICHECK(it != memo_var_.end());
584 std::string print_name = it->second.str();
585
586 std::string name_hint = var->name_hint.operator std::string();
587 if (name_hint.length() == 0 || !std::isalpha(name_hint[0])) {
588 name_hint = "v" + name_hint;
589 }
590 std::replace(name_hint.begin(), name_hint.end(), '.', '_');
591
592 auto it2 = name_alloc_map_.find(name_hint);
593 // Skip it if we can not find the name_hint in name_alloc_map_.
594 if (it2 == name_alloc_map_.end()) return;
595 if (it2->second > 0) {
596 name_hint = name_hint + '_' + std::to_string(it2->second);
597 }
598 // Skip it if the name_hint is not equal to how it should be printed.
599 if (name_hint != print_name) return;
600 // Free the conresponding name_alloc_map_ index
601 --it2->second;
602}
603
604Doc TVMScriptPrinter::PrintMatchBufferRegion(const MatchBufferRegionNode* op) {
605 const Buffer& buf = op->buffer;
606 buf_not_in_headers_.insert(buf.get());
607
608 Doc doc = Print(op->buffer) << " = " << tir_prefix_ << ".match_buffer(" << Print(op->source)
609 << ", " << memo_buf_decl_[op->buffer] << ")";
610 return doc;
611}
612
613// check if all arguments, except the first two, are specified for T.match_buffer
614// if not, then this match buffer is printed out as T.buffer in prim_func arguments
615// and check whether there are undefined variables in the shape/strides.
616bool TVMScriptPrinter::IsSimpleBuffer(const Buffer& buf) {
617 if (memo_var_.find(buf->data) != memo_var_.end()) {
618 return false;
619 }
620 if (!buf->strides.empty()) {
621 return false;
622 }
623 for (const PrimExpr& shp_i : buf->shape) {
624 if (!UndefinedVars(shp_i).empty()) {
625 return false;
626 }
627 }
628 for (const PrimExpr& stride_i : buf->strides) {
629 if (!UndefinedVars(stride_i).empty()) {
630 return false;
631 }
632 }
633 if (!UndefinedVars(buf->elem_offset).empty()) {
634 return false;
635 } else if (buf->elem_offset->IsInstance<IntImmNode>()) {
636 IntImm elem_offset = Downcast<IntImm>(buf->elem_offset);
637 if (elem_offset->value != 0) {
638 return false;
639 }
640 }
641 if (buf.scope() != "global") {
642 return false;
643 }
644 if (buf->data_alignment != runtime::kAllocAlignment) {
645 return false;
646 }
647 if (buf->offset_factor != 1) {
648 return false;
649 }
650 if (buf->buffer_type != BufferType::kDefault) {
651 return false;
652 }
653 if (buf->axis_separators.size()) {
654 return false;
655 }
656 return true;
657}
658
659Doc TVMScriptPrinter::PrintInlineBufferBind(const Buffer& buffer) {
660 Doc doc;
661 doc << tir_prefix_ << ".Buffer[";
662 if (buffer->shape.size() == 1) {
663 doc << Print(buffer->shape[0]);
664 } else {
665 doc << PrintTuple(buffer->shape.as<ArrayNode>());
666 }
667 doc << ", " << PrintDType(buffer->dtype) << "]";
668 return doc;
669}
670
671// print array out as tuple with parentheses
672Doc TVMScriptPrinter::PrintTuple(const ArrayNode* op) {
673 Doc doc;
674 doc << '(';
675 for (size_t i = 0; i < op->size(); ++i) {
676 if (i != 0) {
677 doc << ", ";
678 }
679 doc << Print(op->at(i));
680 }
681 if (op->size() == 1) doc << ",";
682 doc << ')';
683 return doc;
684}
685
686Doc TVMScriptPrinter::PrintCommReducer(const CommReducerNode* op) {
687 Doc doc;
688 int n_var = static_cast<int>(op->rhs.size());
689
690 doc << tir_prefix_ << ".comm_reducer(lambda ";
691 for (const Var& v_lhs : op->lhs) {
692 doc << Print(v_lhs) << ", ";
693 }
694 for (int i = 0; i < n_var; ++i) {
695 doc << Print(op->rhs[i]) << (i == n_var - 1 ? ": " : ", ");
696 }
697 if (n_var == 1) {
698 doc << Print(op->result[0]) << ", ";
699 } else {
700 doc << "(";
701 for (int i = 0; i < n_var; ++i) {
702 doc << Print(op->result[i]);
703 if (i != n_var - 1) {
704 doc << ", ";
705 }
706 }
707 doc << "), ";
708 }
709 doc << Print(op->identity_element) << ")";
710
711 // Remove the vars in `lhs` and `rhs`, because they are the parameters of the printed lambda.
712 for (int i = 0; i < n_var; ++i) {
713 memo_var_.erase(op->lhs[i]);
714 memo_var_.erase(op->rhs[i]);
715 }
716 return doc;
717}
718
719Doc TVMScriptPrinter::Print(const ObjectRef& node) {
720 if (!node.defined()) return Doc::Text("None");
721 if (node->IsInstance<StmtNode>()) {
722 return PrintOptionalInfo(Downcast<Stmt>(node)) << VisitStmt(Downcast<Stmt>(node));
723 } else if (node->IsInstance<PrimExprNode>()) {
724 ExprPrecedence t = ExprPrecedence::kUnknown;
725 return VisitExpr(Downcast<PrimExpr>(node), &t);
726 } else if (node->IsInstance<TypeNode>()) {
727 return VisitType(Downcast<Type>(node));
728 } else if (node->IsInstance<PrimFuncNode>()) {
729 return PrintPrimFunc(Downcast<PrimFunc>(node));
730 } else if (node->IsInstance<IRModuleNode>()) {
731 return PrintIRModule(Downcast<IRModule>(node));
732 } else if (node->IsInstance<ArrayNode>()) {
733 return PrintArray(node.as<ArrayNode>());
734 } else if (node->IsInstance<BufferNode>()) {
735 return PrintBuffer(node.as<BufferNode>());
736 } else if (node->IsInstance<StringObj>()) {
737 return PrintString(node.as<StringObj>());
738 } else if (node->IsInstance<IterVarNode>()) {
739 return PrintIterVar(node.as<IterVarNode>());
740 } else if (node->IsInstance<RangeNode>()) {
741 return PrintRange(node.as<RangeNode>());
742 } else if (node->IsInstance<BufferRegionNode>()) {
743 return PrintBufferRegion(node.as<BufferRegionNode>());
744 } else if (node->IsInstance<MatchBufferRegionNode>()) {
745 return PrintMatchBufferRegion(node.as<MatchBufferRegionNode>());
746 } else if (node->IsInstance<CommReducerNode>()) {
747 return PrintCommReducer(node.as<CommReducerNode>());
748 } else if (node->IsInstance<TargetNode>()) {
749 return PrintTarget(node.as<TargetNode>());
750 } else {
751 LOG(FATAL) << "Do not know how to print " << node->GetTypeKey();
752 return Doc();
753 }
754}

794#define TVM_DECLARE_TVMSCRIPT_PRINTER_BINOP(OpName, OpString, OpPrecedence) \
795 Doc TVMScriptPrinter::VisitExpr_(const OpName* op, ExprPrecedence* out_precedence) { \
796 Doc doc; \
797 ExprPrecedence lhs_precedence = ExprPrecedence::kUnknown; \
798 ExprPrecedence rhs_precedence = ExprPrecedence::kUnknown; \
799 /* Get children expr out_precedence */ \
800 Doc lhs_doc = VisitExpr(op->a, &lhs_precedence); \
801 Doc rhs_doc = VisitExpr(op->b, &rhs_precedence); \
802 ICHECK(lhs_precedence != ExprPrecedence::kUnknown); \
803 ICHECK(rhs_precedence != ExprPrecedence::kUnknown); \
804 /* Update out_precedence of current node. */ \
805 *out_precedence = OpPrecedence; \
806 if (lhs_precedence > OpPrecedence) { \
807 doc << "(" << lhs_doc << ")"; \
808 } else { \
809 doc << lhs_doc; \
810 } \
811 doc << OpString; \
812 if (rhs_precedence >= OpPrecedence) { \
813 doc << "(" << rhs_doc << ")"; \
814 } else { \
815 doc << rhs_doc; \
816 } \
817 return doc; \
818 }
819
820TVM_DECLARE_TVMSCRIPT_PRINTER_BINOP(MulNode, " * ", ExprPrecedence::kMultiplicationDivision)
821TVM_DECLARE_TVMSCRIPT_PRINTER_BINOP(DivNode, " / ", ExprPrecedence::kMultiplicationDivision)
822TVM_DECLARE_TVMSCRIPT_PRINTER_BINOP(FloorDivNode, " // ", ExprPrecedence::kMultiplicationDivision)
823TVM_DECLARE_TVMSCRIPT_PRINTER_BINOP(FloorModNode, " % ", ExprPrecedence::kMultiplicationDivision)
824TVM_DECLARE_TVMSCRIPT_PRINTER_BINOP(AddNode, " + ", ExprPrecedence::kAdditionSubtraction)
825TVM_DECLARE_TVMSCRIPT_PRINTER_BINOP(SubNode, " - ", ExprPrecedence::kAdditionSubtraction)
826TVM_DECLARE_TVMSCRIPT_PRINTER_BINOP(LTNode, " < ", ExprPrecedence::kRelational)
827TVM_DECLARE_TVMSCRIPT_PRINTER_BINOP(LENode, " <= ", ExprPrecedence::kRelational)
828TVM_DECLARE_TVMSCRIPT_PRINTER_BINOP(GTNode, " > ", ExprPrecedence::kRelational)
829TVM_DECLARE_TVMSCRIPT_PRINTER_BINOP(GENode, " >= ", ExprPrecedence::kRelational)
830TVM_DECLARE_TVMSCRIPT_PRINTER_BINOP(EQNode, " == ", ExprPrecedence::kEquality)
831TVM_DECLARE_TVMSCRIPT_PRINTER_BINOP(NENode, " != ", ExprPrecedence::kEquality)
832TVM_DECLARE_TVMSCRIPT_PRINTER_BINOP(AndNode, " and ", ExprPrecedence::kAnd)
833TVM_DECLARE_TVMSCRIPT_PRINTER_BINOP(OrNode, " or ", ExprPrecedence::kOr)

896 << Print(op->index);

898 doc << ", " << Print(op->predicate);

900 doc << ")";
901 }

928Doc TVMScriptPrinter::VisitExpr_(const CallNode* op, ExprPrecedence* out_precedence) {
929 *out_precedence = ExprPrecedence::kIdentity;
930 Doc doc;
931 if (auto* ptr_op = op->op.as<OpNode>()) {
932 std::string name = ptr_op->name;
933 if (name.find("tir.") == 0) {
934 name = tir_prefix_ + "." + name.substr(4);
935 }
936 doc << name << "(";
937 } else {
938 auto* op_gvar = op->op.as<GlobalVarNode>();
939 ICHECK(op_gvar != nullptr);
940 doc << Doc::Text(op_gvar->name_hint) << "(";
941 }
942 std::vector<Doc> args;
943 for (const auto& arg : op->args) {
944 args.push_back(Print(arg));
945 }
946 args.push_back(Doc::Text("dtype=") << PrintDType(op->dtype));
947 doc << PrintSep(args, Doc::Text(", ")) << ")";
948 return doc;
949}

966Doc TVMScriptPrinter::VisitStmt_(const LetStmtNode* op) {
967 if (!buffer_var_usage_.count(op->var)) {
968 buffer_var_usage_ = BufferUsageFinder::FindUsage(std::move(buffer_var_usage_), op->body);
969 }
970 Array<Buffer> buffer_usage = buffer_var_usage_.Get(op->var).value_or({});
971
972 Doc doc;
973 if (current_num_ != num_child_ - 1) {
974 doc << "with " << tir_prefix_ << ".let(" << Print(op->var) << ", " << Print(op->value) << "):";
975 doc << Doc::Indent(
976 4, Doc::NewLine() << PrintNonHeaderBufferDeclarations(buffer_usage) << PrintBody(op->body));
977 } else {
978 if (memo_var_.find(op->var) == memo_var_.end()) var_not_in_headers_.insert(op->var.get());
979 doc << Print(op->var) << ": " << Print(GetType(op->var)) << " = " << Print(op->value)
980 << Doc::NewLine();
981 doc << PrintNonHeaderBufferDeclarations(buffer_usage) << PrintBody(op->body);
982 }
983 return doc;
984}
985
986Doc TVMScriptPrinter::VisitStmt_(const AttrStmtNode* op) {
987 Doc doc;
988 if (op->node.defined()) {
989 // merge attr with realize when possible
990 if (op->node->IsInstance<BufferNode>() && op->attr_key == "realize_scope" &&
991 op->body->IsInstance<BufferRealizeNode>()) {
992 const auto* realize = Downcast<BufferRealize>(op->body).get();
993 if (realize->buffer.same_as(op->node)) {
994 if (current_num_ != num_child_ - 1) {
995 doc << "with " << tir_prefix_ << ".realize(" << Print(realize->buffer)
996 << Print(realize->bounds) << ", " << Print(op->value);
997 if (!is_one(realize->condition)) {
998 doc << ", " << Print(realize->condition);
999 }
1000 doc << "):" << Doc::Indent(4, Doc::NewLine() << PrintBody(realize->body));
1001 } else {
1002 doc << tir_prefix_ << ".realize(" << Print(realize->buffer) << Print(realize->bounds)
1003 << ", " << Print(op->value);
1004 if (!is_one(realize->condition)) {
1005 doc << ", " << Print(realize->condition);
1006 }
1007 doc << ")" << Doc::NewLine() << PrintBody(realize->body);
1008 }
1009 return doc;
1010 }
1011 }
1012 // concise thread env
1013 if (op->node->IsInstance<IterVarNode>() &&
1014 (op->attr_key == "thread_extent" || op->attr_key == "virtual_thread")) {
1015 const auto* iter_var = Downcast<IterVar>(op->node).get();
1016 var_not_in_headers_.insert(iter_var->var.get());
1017 var_env_map_[iter_var->var] = iter_var->thread_tag;
1018 if (current_num_ != num_child_ - 1) {
1019 doc << "with " << tir_prefix_ << ".launch_thread(" << Print(iter_var->var) << ", "
1020 << Print(op->value) << "):";
1021 doc << Doc::Indent(4, Doc::NewLine() << PrintBody(op->body));
1022 } else {
1023 doc << tir_prefix_ << ".launch_thread(" << Print(iter_var->var) << ", " << Print(op->value)
1024 << ")";
1025 doc << Doc::NewLine() << PrintBody(op->body);
1026 }
1027 TryDeallocVar(iter_var->var);
1028 return doc;
1029 }
1030 }
1031 // default
1032 if (current_num_ != num_child_ - 1) {
1033 doc << "with " << tir_prefix_ << ".attr(" << Print(op->node) << ", "
1034 << Doc::StrLiteral(op->attr_key) << ", " << Print(op->value) << "):";
1035 doc << Doc::Indent(4, Doc::NewLine() << PrintBody(op->body));
1036 } else {
1037 doc << tir_prefix_ << ".attr(" << Print(op->node) << ", " << Doc::StrLiteral(op->attr_key)
1038 << ", " << Print(op->value) << ")";
1039 doc << Doc::NewLine() << PrintBody(op->body);
1040 }
1041 return doc;
1042}
1043
1044Doc TVMScriptPrinter::VisitStmt_(const AssertStmtNode* op) {
1045 Doc doc;
1046 if (current_num_ != num_child_ - 1) {
1047 doc << "with " << tir_prefix_ << ".Assert(" << Print(op->condition) << ", "
1048 << Print(op->message) << "):";
1049 doc << Doc::Indent(4, Doc::NewLine() << PrintBody(op->body));
1050 } else {
1051 doc << "assert " << Print(op->condition) << ", " << Print(op->message);
1052 doc << Doc::NewLine() << PrintBody(op->body);
1053 }
1054 return doc;
1055}

1070namespace {
1071
1072bool IsAllocateDeclBufferPattern(const AllocateNode* allocate) {
1073 const Var& buffer_var = allocate->buffer_var;
1074 const DeclBufferNode* decl_buffer = allocate->body.as<DeclBufferNode>();
1075 if (!decl_buffer) {
1076 return false;
1077 }
1078 const Buffer& buffer = decl_buffer->buffer;
1079 if (!buffer_var.same_as(buffer->data)) {
1080 return false;
1081 }
1082 if (allocate->dtype != buffer->dtype) {
1083 return false;
1084 }
1085 if (!is_one(allocate->condition)) {
1086 return false;
1087 }
1088 if (allocate->annotations.size()) {
1089 return false;
1090 }
1091 if (allocate->extents.size() != buffer->shape.size()) {
1092 return false;
1093 }
1094 tir::ExprDeepEqual expr_equal;
1095 for (size_t i = 0, n = allocate->extents.size(); i < n; ++i) {
1096 if (!expr_equal(allocate->extents[i], buffer->shape[i])) {
1097 return false;
1098 }
1099 }
1100 return true;
1101}
1102
1103} // namespace
1104
1105Doc TVMScriptPrinter::VisitStmt_(const AllocateNode* op) {
1106 var_not_in_headers_.insert(op->buffer_var.get());
1107
1108 if (!buffer_var_usage_.count(op->buffer_var)) {
1109 buffer_var_usage_ = BufferUsageFinder::FindUsage(std::move(buffer_var_usage_), op->body);
1110 }
1111 Array<Buffer> buffer_usage = buffer_var_usage_.Get(op->buffer_var).value_or({});
1112
1113 if (buffer_usage.empty()) {
1114 if (IsAllocateDeclBufferPattern(op)) {
1115 // As a syntax sugar, we identify the pattern of Allocate and DeclBuffer and print a single
1116 // DeclBuffer statement. It is intentionally to call `Print` instead of `PrintBody` here to
1117 // delegate the printing of the current node to `DeclBufferNode` while maintaining the
1118 // same value of `current_num_` and `num_child_`.
1119 return Print(op->body);
1120 }
1121 }
1122
1123 auto storage_scope = GetPtrStorageScope(op->buffer_var);
1124 Doc func_call;
1125 func_call << tir_prefix_ << ".allocate(" << Print(op->extents) << ", " << PrintDType(op->dtype)
1126 << ", " << Print(storage_scope);
1127 if (!is_one(op->condition)) {
1128 func_call << ", " << Print(op->condition);
1129 }
1130 if (!op->annotations.empty()) {
1131 func_call << ", annotations={";
1132 func_call << PrintAnnotations(op->annotations);
1133 func_call << "}";
1134 }
1135 func_call << ")";
1136
1137 Doc doc;
1138 if (current_num_ != num_child_ - 1) {
1139 doc << "with " << func_call << " as " << Print(op->buffer_var) << ":";
1140 doc << Doc::Indent(
1141 4, Doc::NewLine() << PrintNonHeaderBufferDeclarations(buffer_usage) << PrintBody(op->body));
1142 } else {
1143 doc << Print(op->buffer_var) << " = " << func_call << Doc::NewLine();
1144 doc << PrintNonHeaderBufferDeclarations(buffer_usage) << PrintBody(op->body);
1145 }
1146 TryDeallocVar(op->buffer_var);
1147 return doc;
1148}
1149
1150Doc TVMScriptPrinter::VisitStmt_(const AllocateConstNode* alloc) {
1151 std::stringstream ss;
1152 ICHECK(alloc->data) << "Should be presented";
1153 const auto& data = alloc->data.value();
1154
1155 if (alloc->dtype.is_int()) {
1156 if (alloc->dtype.bits() == 8) {
1157 NDArrayToTIR<int8_t>(data, ss);
1158 } else if (alloc->dtype.bits() == 16) {
1159 NDArrayToTIR<int16_t>(data, ss);
1160 } else if (alloc->dtype.bits() == 32) {
1161 NDArrayToTIR<int32_t>(data, ss);
1162 } else if (alloc->dtype.bits() == 64) {
1163 NDArrayToTIR<int64_t>(data, ss);
1164 } else {
1165 LOG(FATAL) << "DataType not supported";
1166 }
1167 } else if (alloc->dtype.is_uint()) {
1168 if (alloc->dtype.bits() == 8) {
1169 // NDArrayToTIR<uint8_t>(data, ss);
1170 } else if (alloc->dtype.bits() == 16) {
1171 NDArrayToTIR<uint16_t>(data, ss);
1172 } else if (alloc->dtype.bits() == 32) {
1173 NDArrayToTIR<uint32_t>(data, ss);
1174 } else if (alloc->dtype.bits() == 64) {
1175 NDArrayToTIR<int64_t>(data, ss);
1176 } else {
1177 LOG(FATAL) << "DataType not supported";
1178 }
1179 } else if (alloc->dtype.is_float()) {
1180 if (alloc->dtype.bits() == 16) {
1181 NDArrayToTIR<int16_t>(data, ss);
1182 } else if (alloc->dtype.bits() == 32) {
1183 NDArrayToTIR<float>(data, ss);
1184 } else if (alloc->dtype.bits() == 64) {
1185 NDArrayToTIR<double>(data, ss);
1186 } else {
1187 LOG(FATAL) << "DataType not supported";
1188 }
1189 } else {
1190 LOG(FATAL) << "DataType not supported";
1191 }
1192 auto ndarray_str = ss.str();
1193
1194 var_not_in_headers_.insert(alloc->buffer_var.get());
1195
1196 if (!buffer_var_usage_.count(alloc->buffer_var)) {
1197 buffer_var_usage_ = BufferUsageFinder::FindUsage(std::move(buffer_var_usage_), alloc->body);
1198 }
1199 Array<Buffer> buffer_usage = buffer_var_usage_.Get(alloc->buffer_var).value_or({});
1200
1201 Doc func_call;
1202 func_call << tir_prefix_ << ".allocate_const(" << ndarray_str << ", " << PrintDType(alloc->dtype)
1203 << ", " << Print(alloc->extents) << ")";
1204
1205 Doc doc;
1206 var_not_in_headers_.insert(alloc->buffer_var.get());
1207 if (current_num_ != num_child_ - 1) {
1208 doc << "with " << func_call << " as " << Print(alloc->buffer_var) << ":";
1209 doc << Doc::Indent(4, Doc::NewLine() << PrintNonHeaderBufferDeclarations(buffer_usage)
1210 << PrintBody(alloc->body));
1211 } else {
1212 doc << Print(alloc->buffer_var) << " = " << func_call << Doc::NewLine();
1213 doc << PrintNonHeaderBufferDeclarations(buffer_usage) << PrintBody(alloc->body);
1214 }
1215 return doc;
1216}
1217
1218Doc TVMScriptPrinter::VisitStmt_(const DeclBufferNode* op) {
1219 const Buffer& buffer = op->buffer;
1220 buf_not_in_headers_.insert(buffer.get());
1221 Doc buffer_name = Print(op->buffer);
1222 Doc func_call;
1223 func_call << tir_prefix_ << ".decl_buffer(" << memo_buf_decl_.at(buffer) << ")";
1224
1225 Doc doc;
1226 if (current_num_ != num_child_ - 1) {
1227 doc << "with " << func_call << " as " << buffer_name << ":";
1228 doc << Doc::Indent(4, Doc::NewLine() << PrintBody(op->body));
1229 } else {
1230 doc << buffer_name << " = " << func_call << Doc::NewLine();
1231 doc << PrintBody(op->body);
1232 }
1233 return doc;
1234}
1235
1236Doc TVMScriptPrinter::VisitStmt_(const IfThenElseNode* op) {
1237 Doc doc;
1238 doc << "if " << Print(op->condition) << ":";
1239 doc << Doc::Indent(4, Doc::NewLine() << PrintBody(op->then_case));
1240 if (!is_one(op->condition) && op->else_case.defined()) {
1241 doc << Doc::NewLine();
1242 doc << "else:" << Doc::Indent(4, Doc::NewLine() << PrintBody(op->else_case));
1243 }
1244 return doc;
1245}
1246
1247Doc TVMScriptPrinter::VisitStmt_(const SeqStmtNode* op) {
1248 std::vector<Doc> stmts;
1249 for (Stmt stmt : op->seq) {
1250 stmts.push_back(Print(stmt));
1251 }
1252 return PrintSep(stmts, Doc::NewLine());
1253}
1254
1255Doc TVMScriptPrinter::VisitStmt_(const EvaluateNode* op) {
1256 if (auto* call = op->value.as<CallNode>()) {
1257 if (call->op.same_as(builtin::assume())) {
1258 Doc doc;
1259 doc << tir_prefix_ << ".assume(" << Print(call->args[0]) << ")";
1260 return doc;
1261 }
1262 }
1263
1264 Doc doc;
1265 doc << tir_prefix_ << ".evaluate(" << Print(op->value) << ")";
1266 return doc;
1267}
1268
1269Doc TVMScriptPrinter::VisitStmt_(const ForNode* op) {
1270 Doc doc;
1271 var_not_in_headers_.insert(op->loop_var.get());
1272 loop_var_map_[op->loop_var.get()] = GetRef<For>(op);
1273 const auto* body = op->body.as<ForNode>();
1274 bool simple_loop = IsSimpleLoop(op);
1275 if (simple_loop) simple_loop_stack_.push_back(GetRef<For>(op));
1276 // It is a loop that can be compressed, let the loops below print it out
1277 if (simple_loop && body != nullptr && IsSimpleLoop(body) && !DependOnPrevLoops(body)) {
1278 doc << Print(GetRef<For>(body));
1279 TryDeallocVar(op->loop_var);
1280 loop_var_map_.erase(op->loop_var.get());
1281 return doc;
1282 }
1283 // It is a loop that can not be compressed
1284 bool print_above = !simple_loop_stack_.empty();
1285 // print loops above if needed
1286 if (print_above) {
1287 doc << PrintLoopStack();
1288 simple_loop_stack_.clear();
1289 }
1290 if (!simple_loop) {
1291 // print current loop if needed
1292 Doc current_loop;
1293 current_loop << PrintLoop(GetRef<For>(op));
1294 current_loop << Doc::Indent(4, Doc::NewLine() << PrintBody(op->body));
1295 doc << (print_above ? Doc::Indent(4, Doc::NewLine() << current_loop) : current_loop);
1296 } else {
1297 doc << Doc::Indent(4, Doc::NewLine() << PrintBody(op->body));
1298 }
1299 TryDeallocVar(op->loop_var);
1300 loop_var_map_.erase(op->loop_var.get());
1301 return doc;
1302}
1303
1304Doc TVMScriptPrinter::VisitStmt_(const PrefetchNode* op) {
1305 Doc doc;
1306 doc << tir_prefix_ << ".prefetch(" << Print(op->buffer) << ", " << Print(op->bounds) << ")";
1307 return doc;
1308}
1309
1310Doc TVMScriptPrinter::VisitStmt_(const WhileNode* op) {
1311 Doc doc;
1312 doc << "while " << Print(op->condition) << ":";
1313 doc << Doc::Indent(4, Doc::NewLine() << PrintBody(op->body));
1314 return doc;
1315}

1317Doc TVMScriptPrinter::VisitType_(const PrimTypeNode* node) {
1318 Doc doc;
1319 doc << tir_prefix_ << ".";
1320 if (node->dtype.is_void()) {
1321 doc << "void";
1322 } else {
1323 doc << runtime::DLDataType2String(node->dtype);
1324 }
1325 return doc;
1326}

1328Doc TVMScriptPrinter::VisitType_(const PointerTypeNode* node) {

1330 doc << tir_prefix_ << ".Ptr[";
1331 doc << Print(node->element_type);
1332 if (!node->storage_scope.empty()) {
1333 doc << ", " << Doc::StrLiteral(node->storage_scope);
1334 }
1335 doc << "]";
1336 return doc;
1337}

1339Doc TVMScriptPrinter::VisitType_(const TupleTypeNode* node) {
1340 if (node->fields.empty()) {
1341 return Doc::Text("None");
1342 } else {

1344 for (Type field : node->fields) {

1348 }

1351Doc TVMScriptPrinter::VisitStmt_(const BufferStoreNode* op) {
1352 Doc doc;
1353 if (op->indices.size() == 0) {
1354 doc << Print(op->buffer) << "[()] = " << Print(op->value);
1355 } else {
1356 doc << Print(op->buffer) << PrintBufferIndices(op->indices) << " = " << Print(op->value);
1357 }
1358 return doc;
1359}
1360
1361/*! Helper functions for block printing. */
1362Doc TVMScriptPrinter::PrintBlockVar(const IterVar& iter_var, const PrimExpr& value) {
1363 Doc doc;
1364 doc << Print(iter_var->var) << " = " << tir_prefix_ << ".axis.";
1365 switch (iter_var->iter_type) {
1366 case kDataPar:
1367 doc << "spatial";
1368 break;
1369 case kCommReduce:
1370 doc << "reduce";
1371 break;
1372 case kOrdered:
1373 doc << "scan";
1374 break;
1375 case kOpaque:
1376 doc << "opaque";
1377 break;
1378 default:
1379 LOG(FATAL) << "Unknown block var iter type: " << iter_var->iter_type;
1380 break;
1381 }
1382 doc << "(";
1383 const Range& dom = iter_var->dom;
1384 if (is_zero(dom->min)) {
1385 doc << Print(dom->extent);
1386 } else {
1387 doc << "(" << Print(dom->min) << ", " << Print(dom->min + dom->extent) << ")";
1388 }
1389 doc << ", " << Print(value) << ")";
1390 return doc;
1391}
1392
1393Doc TVMScriptPrinter::PrintBlockVarRemaps() {
1394 ICHECK(!block_var_remaps_.empty());
1395 if (block_var_remaps_.size() == 1) {
1396 const IterVar& iter_var = block_var_remaps_[0].first;
1397 const PrimExpr& value = block_var_remaps_[0].second;
1398 return PrintBlockVar(iter_var, value);
1399 }
1400 Doc doc;
1401 std::vector<Doc> iter_vars, iter_values;
1402 std::string iter_type;
1403 for (const auto& pair : block_var_remaps_) {
1404 const IterVar& iter_var = pair.first;
1405 const PrimExpr& value = pair.second;
1406 iter_vars.push_back(Print(iter_var->var));
1407 iter_values.push_back(Print(value));
1408 if (iter_var->iter_type == kDataPar) {
1409 iter_type += "S";
1410 } else if (iter_var->iter_type == kCommReduce) {
1411 iter_type += "R";
1412 } else {
1413 ICHECK(false);
1414 }
1415 }
1416 doc << PrintSep(iter_vars, Doc::Text(", ")) << " = " << tir_prefix_ << ".axis.remap("
1417 << Doc::StrLiteral(iter_type) << ", [" << PrintSep(iter_values, Doc::Text(", ")) << "])";
1418 return doc;
1419}
1420
1421Doc TVMScriptPrinter::PrintBlockPredicate(const BlockRealizeNode* op) {
1422 Doc doc;
1423 if (!is_one(op->predicate)) {
1424 doc << Doc::NewLine() << tir_prefix_ << ".where(" << Print(op->predicate) << ")";
1425 }
1426 return doc;
1427}
1428
1429Doc TVMScriptPrinter::PrintBlockVars(const BlockRealizeNode* op) {
1430 Doc doc;
1431 const auto* block_op = op->block.as<BlockNode>();
1432 ICHECK_EQ(block_op->iter_vars.size(), op->iter_values.size());
1433 tir::ExprDeepEqual expr_equal;
1434
1435 auto is_simple_remap = [this, &expr_equal](const IterVar& iter_var,
1436 const PrimExpr& value) -> bool {
1437 if (iter_var->iter_type != kDataPar && iter_var->iter_type != kCommReduce) return false;
1438 if (!value->IsInstance<VarNode>()) return false;
1439 const Var& var = Downcast<Var>(value);
1440 auto it = loop_var_map_.find(var.get());
1441 return it != loop_var_map_.end() && expr_equal(it->second->min, iter_var->dom->min) &&
1442 expr_equal(it->second->extent, iter_var->dom->extent);
1443 };
1444
1445 for (size_t i = 0; i < block_op->iter_vars.size(); ++i) {
1446 const IterVar& iter_var = block_op->iter_vars[i];
1447 const PrimExpr& value = op->iter_values[i];
1448 var_not_in_headers_.insert(iter_var->var.get());
1449 if (is_simple_remap(iter_var, value)) {
1450 block_var_remaps_.push_back(std::make_pair(iter_var, value));
1451 } else {
1452 if (!block_var_remaps_.empty()) {
1453 doc << Doc::NewLine() << PrintBlockVarRemaps();
1454 block_var_remaps_.clear();
1455 }
1456 doc << Doc::NewLine() << PrintBlockVar(iter_var, value);
1457 }
1458 }
1459 if (!block_var_remaps_.empty()) {
1460 doc << Doc::NewLine() << PrintBlockVarRemaps();
1461 block_var_remaps_.clear();
1462 }
1463 return doc;
1464}
1465
1466Doc TVMScriptPrinter::PrintBlockAttr(const BlockRealizeNode* op) {
1467 const auto* block_op = op->block.as<BlockNode>();
1468 Doc block_attr_doc;
1469 // print binding, read/write tensor region, annotations
1470 block_attr_doc << Doc::NewLine() << tir_prefix_ << ".reads("
1471 << PrintExpandedArray(block_op->reads.as<ArrayNode>()) << ")";
1472 block_attr_doc << Doc::NewLine() << tir_prefix_ << ".writes("
1473 << PrintExpandedArray(block_op->writes.as<ArrayNode>()) << ")";
1474 if (!block_op->annotations.empty()) {
1475 block_attr_doc << Doc::NewLine() << tir_prefix_ << ".block_attr({";
1476 block_attr_doc << PrintAnnotations(block_op->annotations);
1477 block_attr_doc << "})";
1478 }
1479 return block_attr_doc;
1480}
1481
1482// This function is to make sure arguments of T.reads() and T.writes() is not parsed by printer as a
1483// List. Therefore the brackets are removed before and after printing arguments out
1484Doc TVMScriptPrinter::PrintExpandedArray(const ArrayNode* op) {
1485 Doc doc;
1486 for (size_t i = 0; i < op->size(); ++i) {
1487 if (i != 0) {
1488 doc << ", ";
1489 }
1490 doc << Print(op->at(i));
1491 }
1492 return doc;
1493}
1494
1495Doc TVMScriptPrinter::PrintBlockBody(const BlockNode* op) {
1496 Doc body;
1497 for (const auto& alloc_buf : op->alloc_buffers) {
1498 buf_not_in_headers_.insert(alloc_buf.get());
1499 body << Print(alloc_buf) << " = " << tir_prefix_ << ".alloc_buffer("
1500 << memo_buf_decl_[alloc_buf] << ")" << Doc::NewLine();
1501 }
1502 for (const auto& match_buf : op->match_buffers) {
1503 body << Print(match_buf) << Doc::NewLine();
1504 }
1505 if (op->init.defined()) {
1506 Doc init_block;
1507 init_block << "with " << tir_prefix_ << ".init():";
1508 init_block << Doc::Indent(4, Doc::NewLine() << PrintBody(op->init.value()));
1509 body << init_block << Doc::NewLine();
1510 }
1511 body << PrintBody(op->body);
1512 return body;
1513}
1514
1515/*!
1516 * \brief Print the name of a block
1517 * \param block_op The block node to be printed
1518 */
1519Doc TVMScriptPrinter::PrintBlockName(const BlockNode* block_op) {
1520 Doc doc;
1521 doc << "with " << tir_prefix_ << ".block(";
1522 if (!block_op->name_hint.empty()) {
1523 doc << Doc::StrLiteral(block_op->name_hint);
1524 }
1525 doc << "):";
1526 return doc;
1527}
1528
1529Doc TVMScriptPrinter::VisitStmt_(const BlockRealizeNode* op) {
1530 const auto* block_op = op->block.as<BlockNode>();
1531 Doc doc = PrintOptionalInfo(GetRef<Stmt>(block_op));
1532 // print block name
1533 doc << PrintBlockName(block_op);
1534 // Print block predicate.
1535 Doc block_predicate = PrintBlockPredicate(op);
1536 // Print the variable bindings, valid to use in block attributes and
1537 // body
1538 Doc block_var = PrintBlockVars(op);
1539 // print read/write tensor region, annotations
1540 Doc block_attr_doc = PrintBlockAttr(op);
1541 // print body
1542 Doc body = PrintBlockBody(block_op);
1543 doc << Doc::Indent(4, block_predicate << block_var << block_attr_doc << Doc::NewLine() << body);
1544 for (const auto& iter_var : block_op->iter_vars) {
1545 TryDeallocVar(iter_var->var);
1546 }
1547 return doc;
1548}
1549
1550Doc TVMScriptPrinter::PrintBody(const Stmt& body) {
1551 int memo_num_child, memo_current_num;
1552 std::swap(memo_num_child, num_child_);
1553 std::swap(memo_current_num, current_num_);
1554
1555 Doc doc;
1556 if (body->IsInstance<SeqStmtNode>()) {
1557 const auto& op = Downcast<SeqStmt>(body);
1558 num_child_ = op->seq.size();
1559 current_num_ = 0;
1560 std::vector<Doc> stmts;
1561 for (Stmt stmt : op->seq) {
1562 stmts.push_back(Print(stmt));
1563 current_num_++;
1564 }
1565 doc = PrintSep(stmts, Doc::NewLine());
1566 } else {
1567 num_child_ = 1;
1568 current_num_ = 0;
1569 doc = Print(body);
1570 }
1571
1572 std::swap(memo_num_child, num_child_);
1573 std::swap(memo_current_num, current_num_);
1574 return doc;
1575}
1576
1577Doc TVMScriptPrinter::PrintIRModule(const IRModule& module) {
1578 auto* op = module.operator->();
1579 Doc doc;
1580 doc << "@tvm.script.ir_module" << Doc::NewLine();
1581 doc << "class Module:";
1582 for (const auto& x : op->functions) {
1583 func2var_[x.second.operator->()] = x.first;
1584 }
1585 Doc body = Doc::NewLine();
1586 std::vector<Doc> functions;
1587 for (auto it = op->functions.begin(); it != op->functions.end(); ++it) {
1588 if ((*it).second.as<PrimFuncNode>()) {
1589 functions.push_back(Print((*it).second));
1590 }
1591 }
1592 body << TVMScriptPrinter::PrintSep(functions, Doc::NewLine() << Doc::NewLine());
1593 body << Doc::NewLine() << DumpMeta();
1594 doc << Doc::Indent(4, body);
1595 return doc;
1596}
1597
1598Doc TVMScriptPrinter::PrintPrimFunc(const PrimFunc& primFunc) {
1599 auto* op = primFunc.operator->();
1600 // clear renaming map
1601 memo_var_.clear();
1602 memo_buf_.clear();
1603 memo_buf_decl_.clear();
1604 var_not_in_headers_.clear();
1605 buf_not_in_headers_.clear();
1606 // print signature
1607 Doc doc;
1608 doc << "@" << tir_prefix_ << ".prim_func" << Doc::NewLine();
1609 doc << "def " << (func2var_.find(op) == func2var_.end() ? "func" : func2var_[op]->name_hint)
1610 << "(";
1611 std::vector<Doc> params;
1612 std::unordered_set<Buffer, ObjectPtrHash, ObjectPtrEqual> simple_buf;
1613 for (const auto& param : op->params) {
1614 var_not_in_headers_.insert(param.get());
1615 auto it = op->buffer_map.find(param);
1616 // check if this param is a T.handle
1617 if (it != op->buffer_map.end()) {
1618 // check if this match_buffer has only the first two arguments specified
1619 // and whether the match_buffer is a dynamic buffer.
1620 const Buffer& buf = (*it).second;
1621 if (IsSimpleBuffer(buf)) {
1622 simple_buf.insert(buf);
1623 buf_not_in_headers_.insert(buf.get());
1624 params.push_back(Print(buf) << ": " << PrintInlineBufferBind(buf));
1625 continue;
1626 }
1627 }
1628 params.push_back(Print(param) << ": " << Print(GetType(param)));
1629 }
1630 doc << PrintSep(params, Doc::Text(", ")) << ") -> " << Print(primFunc->ret_type) << ":";
1631
1632 Doc body = Doc::NewLine();
1633 // print buffer_bind
1634 for (const auto& param : op->params) {
1635 auto it = op->buffer_map.find(param);
1636 if (it == op->buffer_map.end()) continue;
1637 const Buffer& buf = (*it).second;
1638 if (simple_buf.count(buf)) continue;
1639 buf_not_in_headers_.insert(buf.get());
1640 body << Print(buf) << " = " << tir_prefix_ << ".match_buffer(";
1641 ICHECK(memo_buf_decl_.count(buf));
1642 body << Print((*it).first) << ", " << memo_buf_decl_[buf];
1643 body << ")" << Doc::NewLine();
1644 }
1645 // print preflattened buffer map
1646 for (const auto& param : op->params) {
1647 auto pf_buf_it = op->preflattened_buffer_map.find(param);
1648 if (pf_buf_it != op->preflattened_buffer_map.end()) {
1649 const Buffer& preflattened = (*pf_buf_it).second;
1650
1651 auto buf_it = op->buffer_map.find(param);
1652 ICHECK(buf_it != op->buffer_map.end()) << "Found pre-flattened buffer " << preflattened->name
1653 << " with no corresponding post-flatten buffer.";
1654 const Buffer& postflattened = (*buf_it).second;
1655
1656 // Call Print() without assigning in order to fill memo_buf_decl_.
1657 Print(preflattened);
1658 buf_not_in_headers_.insert(preflattened.get());
1659 ICHECK(memo_buf_decl_.count(preflattened));
1660
1661 body << tir_prefix_ << ".preflattened_buffer(" << Print(postflattened) << ", "
1662 << memo_buf_decl_.at(preflattened) << ")" << Doc::NewLine();
1663 }
1664 }
1665 // print body
1666 body << "# body" << Doc::NewLine();
1667
1668 Optional<Block> elided_root_block_body = [&]() -> Optional<Block> {
1669 auto block_realize = op->body.as<BlockRealizeNode>();
1670 if (!block_realize || block_realize->iter_values.size()) {
1671 return NullOpt;
1672 }
1673
1674 const auto& block = block_realize->block;
1675 if (block->annotations.size() || ContainsOptionalInfo(block)) {
1676 return NullOpt;
1677 }
1678
1679 // The autocomplete might recognize the body itself as being a
1680 // root block, and fail to insert it.
1681 bool autocomplete_would_insert_root_block = [&]() -> bool {
1682 if (block->alloc_buffers.size()) {
1683 return true;
1684 }
1685
1686 auto* block_realize = block->body.as<BlockRealizeNode>();
1687 if (block_realize && block_realize->block->iter_vars.size()) {
1688 return true;
1689 }
1690 if (!block_realize && ContainsNode<BlockRealizeNode>(block->body)) {
1691 return true;
1692 }
1693 return false;
1694 }();
1695
1696 if (autocomplete_would_insert_root_block) {
1697 return block;
1698 } else {
1699 return NullOpt;
1700 }
1701 }();
1702
1703 if (elided_root_block_body) {
1704 // Skip printing of root block in cases where tvm::tir::ScriptComplete
1705 // would re-insert it.
1706 body << "# with " << tir_prefix_ << ".block(\"root\")" << Doc::NewLine();
1707 body << PrintBlockBody(elided_root_block_body.value().get());
1708 } else {
1709 // If this is a non-root block, or is an unskippable root block,
1710 // just print it without skipping.
1711 body << PrintBody(op->body);
1712 }
1713
1714 // print func attrs
1715 Doc header_attr;
1716 if (primFunc->attrs.defined()) {
1717 header_attr << Doc::NewLine() << "# function attr dict" << Doc::NewLine() << tir_prefix_
1718 << ".func_attr({";
1719 std::vector<Doc> attrs;
1720 for (const auto& it : op->attrs->dict) {
1721 attrs.push_back(Doc::StrLiteral(it.first) << ": " << Print(it.second));
1722 }
1723 header_attr << PrintSep(attrs, Doc::Text(", ")) << "})";
1724 }
1725 // print buffer declarations(buffers not defined by buffer_bind or buffer_allocate)
1726 Doc header_buf;
1727 std::vector<const BufferNode*> bufs;
1728 for (const auto& it : memo_buf_) {
1729 if (buf_not_in_headers_.find(it.first.get()) == buf_not_in_headers_.end()) {
1730 bufs.push_back(it.first.get());
1731 }
1732 }
1733 if (!bufs.empty()) {
1734 header_buf << Doc::NewLine() << "# buffer definition";
1735 std::sort(bufs.begin(), bufs.end(), [&](const BufferNode* a, const BufferNode* b) {
1736 return memo_buf_[GetRef<Buffer>(a)].str() < memo_buf_[GetRef<Buffer>(b)].str();
1737 });
1738 for (const auto& buf : bufs) {
1739 header_buf << Doc::NewLine() << Print(GetRef<Buffer>(buf)) << " = " << tir_prefix_
1740 << ".buffer_decl(";
1741 header_buf << memo_buf_decl_[GetRef<Buffer>(buf)] << ")";
1742 }
1743 }
1744 // print var declaration
1745 Doc header_var;
1746 std::vector<const VarNode*> vars;
1747 for (const auto& it : memo_var_) {
1748 if (var_not_in_headers_.find(it.first.get()) == var_not_in_headers_.end()) {
1749 vars.push_back(it.first.get());
1750 }
1751 }
1752 if (!var_env_map_.empty()) {
1753 header_var << Doc::NewLine() << "# var definition";
1754 for (const auto& it : var_env_map_) {
1755 header_var << Doc::NewLine() << Print(it.first) << " = " << tir_prefix_ << ".env_thread("
1756 << Doc::StrLiteral(it.second) << ")";
1757 }
1758 }
1759 if (!vars.empty()) {
1760 std::sort(vars.begin(), vars.end(), [&](const VarNode* a, const VarNode* b) {
1761 return memo_var_[GetRef<Var>(a)].str() < memo_var_[GetRef<Var>(b)].str();
1762 });
1763 for (const auto& var : vars) {
1764 auto type = GetRef<Var>(var)->type_annotation;
1765 if (auto* ptr_type = type.as<PointerTypeNode>()) {
1766 auto* prim_type = ptr_type->element_type.as<PrimTypeNode>();
1767 ICHECK(prim_type);
1768 header_var << Doc::NewLine() << Print(GetRef<Var>(var)) << " = " << tir_prefix_
1769 << ".buffer_var(";
1770 header_var << PrintDType(prim_type->dtype) << ", "
1771 << Doc::StrLiteral(ptr_type->storage_scope) << ")";
1772 } else {
1773 header_var << Doc::NewLine() << Print(GetRef<Var>(var)) << " = " << tir_prefix_ << ".var(";
1774 header_var << PrintDType(var->dtype) << ")";
1775 }
1776 }
1777 }
1778 doc << Doc::Indent(4, header_attr << header_var << header_buf << body);
1779 return doc;
1780}
1781
1782Doc TVMScriptPrinter::PrintArray(const ArrayNode* op) {
1783 Doc doc;
1784 doc << '[';
1785 for (size_t i = 0; i < op->size(); ++i) {
1786 if (i != 0) {
1787 doc << ", ";
1788 }
1789 doc << Print(op->at(i));
1790 }
1791 doc << ']';
1792 return doc;
1793}
1794
1795Doc TVMScriptPrinter::PrintIterVar(const IterVarNode* op) {
1796 Doc doc;
1797 doc << tir_prefix_ << ".iter_var(" << Print(op->var);
1798 if (op->dom.defined()) {
1799 doc << ", [" << Print(op->dom) << "], ";
1800 } else {
1801 doc << ", None, ";
1802 }
1803 doc << Doc::StrLiteral(IterVarType2String(op->iter_type)) << ", ";
1804 doc << Doc::StrLiteral(op->thread_tag) << ")";
1805 return doc;
1806}
1807
1808Doc TVMScriptPrinter::PrintRange(const RangeNode* op) {
1809 return Print(op->min) << ":" << Print(op->min + op->extent);
1810}
1811
1812Doc TVMScriptPrinter::PrintBuffer(const BufferNode* op) {
1813 const Buffer& buffer = GetRef<Buffer>(op);
1814 return meta_.InMeta(buffer) ? meta_.GetMetaNode(buffer) : AllocBuf(buffer);
1815}
1816
1817Doc TVMScriptPrinter::PrintBufferIndices(const Array<PrimExpr>& indices) {
1818 Doc doc;
1819 doc << '[';
1820 for (size_t i = 0; i < indices.size(); ++i) {
1821 if (i != 0) {
1822 doc << ", ";
1823 }
1824 PrimExpr index = indices[i];
1825 if (const RampNode* ramp = index.as<RampNode>()) {
1826 // specify ramp printing as python index slice
1827 if (auto* stride_imm = ramp->stride.as<IntImmNode>()) {
1828 doc << Print(ramp->base) << ":" << Print(ramp->base + ramp->lanes * ramp->stride);
1829 if (stride_imm->value != 1) {
1830 doc << ":" << Print(ramp->stride);
1831 }
1832 continue;
1833 }
1834 }
1835 doc << Print(index);
1836 }
1837 doc << ']';
1838 return doc;
1839}
1840
1841Doc TVMScriptPrinter::PrintNonHeaderBufferDeclarations(const Array<Buffer>& aliasing_buffers) {
1842 Doc decls;
1843 for (const auto& buf_usage : aliasing_buffers) {
1844 decls << Print(buf_usage) << " = " << tir_prefix_ << ".buffer_decl("
1845 << memo_buf_decl_[buf_usage] << ")" << Doc::NewLine();
1846 buf_not_in_headers_.insert(buf_usage.get());
1847 }
1848 return decls;
1849}
1850
1851Doc TVMScriptPrinter::PrintBufferRegion(const BufferRegionNode* op) {
1852 Doc doc;
1853 if (op->region.size() == 0) {
1854 doc << Print(op->buffer) << "[()]";
1855 } else {
1856 doc << Print(op->buffer) << "[";
1857 for (size_t i = 0; i < op->region.size(); ++i) {
1858 if (i != 0) doc << ", ";
1859 const auto& range = op->region[i];
1860 if (!is_one(range->extent)) {
1861 doc << Print(range->min) << " : " << Print(ana_.Simplify(range->min + range->extent));
1862 } else {
1863 doc << Print(range->min);
1864 }
1865 }
1866 doc << "]";
1867 }
1868 return doc;
1869}
1870
1871Doc TVMScriptPrinter::PrintAnnotations(const Map<String, ObjectRef>& annotations) {
1872 Doc res;
1873 std::vector<std::pair<String, ObjectRef>> anno_list;
1874 anno_list.reserve(annotations.size());
1875 for (const auto& pair : annotations) {
1876 anno_list.emplace_back(pair);
1877 }
1878 sort(anno_list.begin(), anno_list.end());
1879 for (size_t i = 0; i < anno_list.size(); ++i) {
1880 if (i != 0) {
1881 res << ", ";
1882 }
1883 res << "\"" << anno_list[i].first << "\":" << Print(anno_list[i].second);
1884 }
1885 return res;
1886}
1887
1888Doc TVMScriptPrinter::PrintLoop(const For& loop) {
1889 Doc res;
1890 res << "for " << Print(loop->loop_var) << " in " << tir_prefix_
1891 << "." + std::string(ForKind2String(loop->kind)) + "(";
1892 if (is_zero(loop->min)) {
1893 res << Print(loop->extent);
1894 } else {
1895 res << Print(loop->min) << ", " << Print(ana_.Simplify(loop->min + loop->extent));
1896 }
1897 if (loop->thread_binding.defined()) {
1898 res << ", thread=";
1899 res << Print(loop->thread_binding.value()->thread_tag);
1900 }
1901 if (!loop->annotations.empty()) {
1902 res << ", annotations={";
1903 res << PrintAnnotations(loop->annotations);
1904 res << "}";
1905 }
1906 res << "):";
1907 return res;
1908}
1909
1910Doc TVMScriptPrinter::PrintLoopStack() {
1911 Doc res;
1912 if (simple_loop_stack_.size() == 1) {
1913 res << PrintLoop(simple_loop_stack_[0]);
1914 } else if (simple_loop_stack_.size() > 1) {
1915 std::vector<Doc> vars, extents;
1916 for (const auto& loop : simple_loop_stack_) {
1917 vars.push_back(Print(loop->loop_var));
1918 extents.push_back(Print(loop->extent));
1919 }
1920 res << "for " << PrintSep(vars, Doc::Text(", ")) << " in " << tir_prefix_ << ".grid("
1921 << PrintSep(extents, Doc::Text(", ")) << "):";
1922 }
1923 return res;
1924}
1925
1926Doc TVMScriptPrinter::PrintTarget(const TargetNode* target) {
1927 Doc res;
1928 res << tir_prefix_ << ".target({";
1929 Map<String, ObjectRef> config = target->Export();
1930 for (auto it = config.begin(); it != config.end(); ++it) {
1931 if (it != config.begin()) {
1932 res << ", ";
1933 }
1934 res << "\"" << (*it).first << "\":";
1935 if ((*it).first == "host") {
1936 ICHECK(target->host.defined());
1937 res << PrintTarget(target->GetHost().value().get());
1938 } else {
1939 res << Print((*it).second);
1940 }
1941 }
1942 res << "})";
1943 return res;
1944}

1946/*!
1947 * \brief The printer for TVMScript with diagnostic
1948 * \details The printer obtain the precedence of the top-level operation when printing each
1949 * subexpression to decide whether or not parentheses is needed.
1950 */
1951class TVMScriptPrinterWithDiagnostic : public TVMScriptPrinter {
1952 public:
1953 explicit TVMScriptPrinterWithDiagnostic(const String& tir_prefix, bool show_meta,
1954 runtime::TypedPackedFunc<std::string(Stmt)> annotate)
1955 : TVMScriptPrinter(tir_prefix, show_meta, annotate) {}
1956
1957 protected:
1958 Doc PrintBlockName(const BlockNode* block_op) override;
1959 Doc PrintUnderline(const Stmt& stmt, int length);
1960 Doc PrintLoop(const For& loop) override;
1961};
1962
1963Doc TVMScriptPrinterWithDiagnostic::PrintBlockName(const BlockNode* block_op) {
1964 Doc doc = TVMScriptPrinter::PrintBlockName(block_op);
1965 doc << PrintUnderline(GetRef<Stmt>(block_op), doc.str().size());
1966 return doc;
1967}
1968
1969Doc TVMScriptPrinterWithDiagnostic::PrintUnderline(const Stmt& stmt, int length) {
1970 Doc doc;
1971 // annotation
1972 if (ContainsOptionalInfo(stmt)) {
1973 String underline = std::string(length, '^');
1974 doc << Doc::NewLine() << underline;
1975 }
1976 return doc;
1977}
1978
1979Doc TVMScriptPrinterWithDiagnostic::PrintLoop(const For& loop) {
1980 Doc res = TVMScriptPrinter::PrintLoop(loop);
1981 res << PrintUnderline(loop, res.str().size());
1982 return res;
1983}
1984
1985String AsTVMScript(const ObjectRef& mod, const String& tir_prefix, bool show_meta) {
1986 ICHECK(mod->IsInstance<PrimFuncNode>() || mod->IsInstance<IRModuleNode>());
1987 Doc doc;
1988 doc << TVMScriptPrinter::PrintHeader(tir_prefix)
1989 << TVMScriptPrinter(tir_prefix, show_meta).Print(mod);
1990 return doc.str() + "\n";
1991}
1992
1993TVM_REGISTER_GLOBAL("script.AsTVMScript").set_body_typed(AsTVMScript);
1994
1995String AsTVMScriptWithDiagnostic(const ObjectRef& mod, const String& tir_prefix, bool show_meta,
1996 runtime::TypedPackedFunc<std::string(Stmt)> annotate) {
1997 ICHECK(mod->IsInstance<PrimFuncNode>() || mod->IsInstance<IRModuleNode>());
1998 Doc doc;
1999 doc << TVMScriptPrinter::PrintHeader(tir_prefix)
2000 << TVMScriptPrinterWithDiagnostic(tir_prefix, show_meta, annotate).Print(mod);
2001 return doc.str() + "\n";
2002}

2004TVM_REGISTER_GLOBAL("script.AsTVMScriptWithDiagnostic").set_body_typed(AsTVMScriptWithDiagnostic);
